Task 12 — Stderr Evidence
========================

Command: cargo run -- --debug tests/fixtures/user-bash-failure.dyyl

Stderr output:
line 1: user.bash — command 'false' failed with status exit status: 1

This confirms:
- Debug warnings are emitted to stderr when user.bash fails
- The warning includes line number (1), command name (user.bash), the failing command text ('false'), and the exit status
- The stdout output is -1 (the failure sentinel)
